{
  "text": "However, the results regarding the hypothesized relationships for family involvement were somewhat more mixed. Family involvement was related to family interfering with work, \u03b2 = .15, t(142) = 1.80, p < .05. This finding was in keeping with [CITATION_1] findings that a high degree of family involvement was related family interfering with work. This relationship may come about when workers with family involvement have difficulty balancing the demands of family roles with the demands of work roles.",
